        <p>A modern, well-fitted bathroom can increase Liverpool property value by up to 5%. On a property worth £200,000, that is a £10,000 uplift from an investment starting at £4,500. Liverpool estate agents consistently identify bathroom quality as one of the top three factors buyers consider when making an offer, alongside kitchen quality and overall condition.</p>
        <p>A tired or poorly maintained bathroom is one of the most common reasons Liverpool buyers reduce their offer or use a property survey as leverage to negotiate. A new bathroom removes this objection entirely and often recovers more than its cost in the final sale price. We offer free surveys for Liverpool homeowners considering a bathroom renovation before listing their property for sale.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="pf-card pf-card-navy" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>Bathroom Renovation for Liverpool Landlords</h3>
        <p>A modern, functional bathroom significantly improves the rental yield and tenant retention of a Liverpool rental property. Tenants in Liverpool's competitive rental market compare properties carefully, and a dated bathroom is consistently cited as a reason to choose a different property. A supply and fit bathroom renovation from £4,500 on a Liverpool rental property typically recovers its cost within 18 to 24 months through reduced void periods and improved rental rates.</p>
        <p>We work with Liverpool landlords across all postcodes and can often coordinate tenant access and work within tight void periods to minimise income loss between tenancies.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
