  <!-- VICTORIAN PROPERTIES -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Bathroom Fitting in Liverpool's Victorian and Period Properties</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Liverpool's Victorian terraces and Edwardian semis present specific challenges for bathroom renovation. Our 30 years of experience in Liverpool's housing stock means we anticipate problems before they happen.</p>

      <div class="pf-card pf-card-navy" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>What Makes Victorian Liverpool Bathrooms Different</h3>
        <p>Many of Liverpool's Victorian terraces have bathrooms in positions that were added as later extensions, over an outrigger, converted from a bedroom, or installed in a ground-floor extension. Waste pipes in these positions often require longer runs to connect to the soil stack, and the existing joists may need reinforcement to support a new bath.</p>
        <p>Solid brick walls in Victorian properties cannot have pipes chased in as easily as cavity walls. Supply pipes are usually surface-run in neat boxing or run under floorboards. We assess all of this at the free survey and plan the installation accordingly. Victorian properties with original cast iron waste pipes may require sections to be replaced where they have corroded, which we identify and include in the quote before work begins.</p>
        <p>For period properties where preserving original features is important, we plan the installation to avoid damaging original coving, picture rails, skirting boards and other period details wherever possible.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

